### Root Cause
The `--min-length` argument in the [build_parser](file:///home/forcewake/coding-agent-battles-init/runs/2026-06-22-bb-001-broken-cli-argument/agents/agy/workspace/bb001_wordfreq/cli.py#L21) function was defined with `action="store_true"`. This caused the parser to treat `--min-length` as a boolean flag that takes no parameters, resulting in subsequent command-line arguments being parsed incorrectly.

### Solution
Modified [cli.py](file:///home/forcewake/coding-agent-battles-init/runs/2026-06-22-bb-001-broken-cli-argument/agents/agy/workspace/bb001_wordfreq/cli.py) to use `type=int` instead
I will re-run the tests using pytest to verify that the environment remains in a healthy state and all tests are passing.
I have verified that all the tests in the workspace are passing. 

The issue in [cli.py](file:///home/forcewake/coding-agent-battles-init/runs/2026-06-22-bb-001-broken-cli-argument/agents/agy/workspace/bb001_wordfreq/cli.py) has been successfully fixed by changing the `--min-length` argument parser definition from `action="store_true"` to `type=int`. Let me know if there's anything else you need!
